<h1 class="display-4">Provisioning manifest</h1>

<hr class="my-4">

<% if manifest.content["providers"]["aws"] %>
  <p>
    Export your <a href="http://docs.aws.amazon.com/general/latest/gr/managing-aws-access-keys.html">AWS access key</a>
    and run the provisioning script to create your platform:
  </p>

  <pre class="p-3 my-4 text-console bg-console border border-dark rounded"><code><%= render "console_aws_provisioning" %></code></pre>
<% else %>
  <p>
    Export your <a href="https://cloud.digitalocean.com/settings/api/tokens">DigitalOcean token</a>
    and run the provisioning script to create your platform:
  </p>

  <pre class="p-3 my-4 text-console bg-console border border-dark rounded"><code><%= render "console_digitalocean_provisioning" %></code></pre>
<% end %>

<hr class="my-4">

<p>What this script does is install the <a href="https://rubygems.org/gems/provisioning">provisioning gem</a>, download the manifest file, look for missing stuff like your SSH public key, and run it:</p>

<pre class="p-3 my-4 text-console bg-console border border-dark rounded"><code><%= render "console_manual_provisioning" %></code></pre>

<hr class="my-4">

<p>This provisioning manifest will be automatically deleted in less than 24 hours.</p>

<div class="text-center">
  <%= link_to "Delete now", manifest, data: { confirm: "Are you sure?" }, method: :delete, class: "btn btn-lg btn-outline-danger", role: "button" %>
</div>
